The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Srivats helps India colts 

 to 159-run win

Mumbai: Srivats Goswami (77) and Tanmay Srivastava (66) helped India under-19 whipp Sri Lanka under-19 by 159 runs in their opening one-day tri-series match in Colombo on Friday. 

The other team playing the series is Bangladesh. 

Opting to bat, the Indian team piled up 277 for five in 50 overs and then skittled out the hosts for 118 in 38 overs. 

Goswamis 77 came off 108 balls with seven fours while skipper Srivastava cracked 66 in 98 balls with three hits to the fences. 

Useful contributions also came from Virat Kohli (38 in 86 balls, three fours and one six) and Saurabh Tiwari (32 not out in 19 balls with two sixes). 

In reply, the Lankans were unable to negotiate the wiles of medium pacer Ravindra Jadeja and spinner Iqbal Abdullah who shared six wickets equally among themselves. 

Indians take on Bangladesh in their next match of the series on Sunday at P. Sara Stadium. 

 BRIEF SCORES 

India U-19 277/5 (Srivats Goswami 77, Tanmay Srivastava 66, Virat Kohli 38, Saurabh Tiwari 32 . .; S. Pathirana 3/49). Sri Lanka U-19 118 all out in 38 ovs (Ravindra Jadeja 3/23, Iqbal Abdullah 3/14). India U-19 won by 159 runs. 

 (PTI) 




